article.headline: La Salle 86, Central Connecticut State 73
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Rodney Green scored 25 points to help La Salle hold off Central Connecticut State for an 86-73 victory Saturday. The Explorers (5-2) led by three points with five minutes left, but effective free throw shooting helped them pull away. Obie Nwadike led Central (3-8) with 27 points and 11 rebounds, while Javier Mojica had 14 points. Green was 11-for-14 from the field.
